            <title><![CDATA[Report: Amazon Working On Mass Effect TV Show]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/mass-effect-tv-show-movie-amazon-live-action-fallout-1851692186</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/report-amazon-working-on-mass-effect-tv-show.1030392/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/mass-effect-tv-show-movie-amazon-live-action-fallout-1851692186<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><figure id="" data-id="9965a243e22eef65f2eb5a4c2e41498d" data-recommend-id="image://9965a243e22eef65f2eb5a4c2e41498d" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="An image shows Shepard from Mass Effect 3. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An image shows Shepard from Mass Effect 3. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Bioware / EA</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="9965a243e22eef65f2eb5a4c2e41498d" data-recommend-id="image://9965a243e22eef65f2eb5a4c2e41498d" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="An image shows Shepard from Mass Effect 3. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>A new report claims that Amazon is officially developing a TV show based on Bioware’s hit sci-fi franchise, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/musings-of-a-mass-effect-1-newcomer-1846994344?_gl=1*1soucfn*_ga*ODA3ODMxOTY3LjE3MzA0ODgyOTc.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTAxNDk1Ni4xNy4wLjE3MzEwMTQ5NTYuNjAuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/musings-of-a-mass-effect-1-newcomer-1846994344?_gl=1*1soucfn*_ga*ODA3ODMxOTY3LjE3MzA0ODgyOTc.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMTAxNDk1Ni4xNy4wLjE3MzEwMTQ5NTYuNjAuMC4w"><em>Mass Effect</em></a></span>. This follows previous reports indicating that Amazon wanted to make a <em>Mass Effect</em> show. Seems the retail giant is finally doing it. </p><div><h4>Suggested Reading</h4></div><div data-video-id="196742" data-monetizable="true" data-position="sidebar" data-video-title="What Is Dragonsplague? Dragon’s Dogma 2’s Devastating Contagion Explained" data-video-blog-id="9" data-video-network="kotaku" data-video-duration="254" data-playlist="196742,196452,195150" data-current="196742"><div><p>What Is Dragonsplague? Dragon’s Dogma 2’s Devastating Contagion Explained</p></div><video disablepictureinpicture="" muted="" playsinline="" width="100%" height="100%" crossorigin="anonymous" preload="none"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/196742/196742_240p.mp4" label="240p" type="video/mp4"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/196742/196742_480p.mp4" label="480p" type="video/mp4"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/196742/196742_720p.mp4" label="720p" type="video/mp4"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/196742/196742_1080p.mp4" label="1080p" type="video/mp4"><track kind="captions" label="English" src="https://kinja.com/api/videoupload/caption/22297.vtt" srclang="en"></video><div><ul><li data-label="">Off</li><li data-label="English">English</li></ul></div></div><div><h4>Suggested Reading</h4></div><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://variety.com/2024/tv/news/mass-effect-tv-series-amazon-writer-marvel-1236203755/&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://variety.com/2024/tv/news/mass-effect-tv-series-amazon-writer-marvel-1236203755/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">In a new report from <em>Variety</em></a></span>, the outlet says the yet-to-be-announced <em>Mass Effect</em> television show will be written and executive-produced by Daniel Casey. The show is being produced by Amazon MGM Studios. No plot details or casting was confirmed by <em>Variety</em>. Casey previously worked on the screenplay for <em>F9: The Fast Saga. </em>He also worked on the sci-fi film <em>Kin, </em>and he did rewrites on <em>10</em> <em>Cloverfield Lane. </em></p><p>In 2021,<span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/report-amazon-wants-to-make-a-mass-effect-series-1848113923&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/report-amazon-wants-to-make-a-mass-effect-series-1848113923"> it was previously reported</a></span> that Amazon wanted to develop a TV show based on the sci-fi RPG franchise after previous, unrelated plans to create a <em>Mass Effect</em> movie fell apart.</p><p>The news arrives on November 7, which is known as N7 Day in the <em>Mass Effect</em> fandom, a day that often brings new announcements about the series. Bioware had warned folks that this <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-mass-effect-n7-day-armor-location-1851692131&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-mass-effect-n7-day-armor-location-1851692131">year’s N7 Day would be a bit quieter</a></span> compared to past years due to the recent release of <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-4-review-dreadwolf-rook-action-rpg-1851681954&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-4-review-dreadwolf-rook-action-rpg-1851681954"><em>Dragon Age: Veilguard</em></a></span><em>. </em>Bioware is currently developing the next main entry in the<em> Mass Effect</em> franchise, though we don’t know much about what that game will be at the moment. </p><p> <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/fallout-show-amazon-review-1851400505&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/fallout-show-amazon-review-1851400505">After Amazon’s huge success with the<em> Fallout</em> TV show</a></span> earlier this year, which is already confirmed for a <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/fallout-amazon-tv-show-season-2-confirmed-release-date-1851395200&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/fallout-amazon-tv-show-season-2-confirmed-release-date-1851395200">second season</a></span>, it makes sense that the streamer would fast-track another video game adaptation based on a different, but also popular RPG series. We’ve seen other parts of Hollywood also try to create hits out of video games, like Netflix’s<em> Tomb Raider</em> animated series and HBO’s award-winning<em> Last of Us</em> series. Will <em>Mass Effect</em> connect with audiences like <em>Fallout</em>? We’ll have to wait to find out. </p><p> .<br></p></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
